{"title_page": "Kings Throne Peak", "text_new": "{{Infobox mountain\n| name = Kings Throne Peak\n| photo = Kings Throne Peak.jpg\n| photo_caption = Kings Throne Peak, northeast aspect\n| map =  Canada Yukon\n| map_caption = Location in Yukon, Canada\n| location = [[Kluane National Park]]<br />[[Yukon]], Canada\n| label_position = right\n| elevation_m = 1990\n| elevation_ref = <ref name=\"pb\">{{cite peakbagger|37639|Kings Throne Peak, Yukon Territory|accessdate=2019-12-06}}</ref>\n| prominence_m = 90\n| prominence_ref = <ref name=bivouac/>\n| range = Dalton Range<br />[[Saint Elias Mountains]]<ref name=bivouac>{{cite bivouac|id=28716|name=Kings Throne Peak|accessdate=2019-12-06}}</ref>\n| parent_peak = \n| coordinates = {{coord|60|32|48|N|137|15|33|W|type:mountain_region:CA|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_ref = <ref name=\"pb\"/>\n| topo = [[National Topographic System|NTS]] 115A/11\n| rock =\n| age =\n| first_ascent =\n| easiest_route = Very steep trail<ref name=bivouac/>\n}}\n\n'''Kings Throne Peak''' is a {{Convert|1990|m|ft|lk=off|abbr=off|adj=on}} mountain [[summit]] in the Dalton Range of the [[Saint Elias Mountains]], in [[Kluane National Park and Reserve|Kluane National Park]] of [[Yukon]], [[Canada]]. The mountain is situated above the south shore of [[Kathleen Lake]], {{convert|7.2|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} southeast of [[Mount Worthington (Yukon)|Mount Worthington]] across the lake, and {{convert|27|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-southeast of [[Haines Junction, Yukon]]. The mountain can be seen from the [[Haines Highway]] as it prominently rises {{Convert|1250|m|ft|lk=off|abbr=off|adj=on}} above the lake. The mountain's descriptive name comes from how it is shaped by a [[cirque]] on the north aspect. A [[rock glacier]] descends from the cirque to the lake. A steep five kilometer trail provides access to the amphitheater, and an additional three kilometres on a beaten path reaches the summit via the east ridge. Based on the [[K\u00f6ppen climate classification]], Kings Throne Peak is located in a [[subarctic climate]] with long, cold, snowy winters, and mild summers.<ref name=Peel>{{cite journal | author = Peel, M. C. |author2=Finlayson, B. L. |author3=McMahon, T. A. |last-author-amp=yes | year = 2007 | title = Updated world map of the K\u00f6ppen\u2212Geiger climate classification | journal = Hydrol. Earth Syst. Sci. | volume = 11 | pages = 1633\u20131644 | issn = 1027-5606}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{stack|{{Portal|Mountains}}}}\n*[[List of mountains of Canada]]\n*[[Geography of Yukon]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[File:Kings Throne Peak, Kathleen Lake.jpg|thumb|center|440px|Kings Throne Peak and Kathleen Lake]]\n\n==External links==\n* Parks Canada website: [https://www.pc.gc.ca/en/pn-np/yt/kluane/activ/randonnee-hiking/kings-throne Kings Throne trail]\n* Flickr photo: [https://www.flickr.com/photos/ben_a/14440744537/in/album-72157645213868397/ View of the cirque]\n* Flickr photo: [https://www.flickr.com/photos/tvrdypa/43691157794/in/photolist-29yQB33-2592F47-YSAP3W-YDa7DY-269emM8-uh1srQ-frqSDW-K5TnP8-n6LV9U-G5tDRJ-dvmywV-2hGk7s7-a8vKoo-k7ZGST-c1amqf-kuQUeB-2fP1q7b-khTojV-ktfXjj-ku68a6-WU1uba-2g1XiNV-rkrpmR-MtuLHd-6MvtbH-8CAzWK-Ln6hhQ-cCGLhJ-6MvunZ-6MvpGp-6MzC5Q-cuPpv9-BBmLtd-MPVhba-8Pb8wW-75kMGb-RfgD4Q-d7MoWu-d7MbfS-7EabTs-d7N3Bh-PSUWyR-SnoSDr-syF63-DT1jYu-Hj5pgN-d7MGk7-EhKzyd-8eVpJw-Hj5S9f Kings Throne Peak with Kathleen Lake]\n\n[[Category:Mountains of Yukon]]\n[[Category:Saint Elias Mountains]]\n[[Category:Kluane National Park and Reserve]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox mountain\n| name = Kings Throne Peak\n| photo = Kings Throne Peak.jpg\n| photo_caption = Kings Throne Peak, northeast aspect\n| map =  Canada Yukon\n| map_caption = Location in Yukon, Canada\n| location = [[Kluane National Park]]<br />[[Yukon]], Canada\n| label_position = right\n| elevation_m = 1990\n| elevation_ref = <ref name=\"pb\">{{cite peakbagger|37639|Kings Throne Peak, Yukon Territory|accessdate=2019-12-06}}</ref>\n| prominence_m = 90\n| prominence_ref = <ref name=bivouac/>\n| range = Dalton Range<br />[[Saint Elias Mountains]]<ref name=bivouac>{{cite bivouac|id=28716|name=Kings Throne Peak|accessdate=2019-12-06}}</ref>\n| parent_peak = \n| coordinates = {{coord|60|32|48|N|137|15|33|W|type:mountain_region:CA|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_ref = <ref name=\"pb\"/>\n| topo = [[National Topographic System|NTS]] 115A/11\n| rock =\n| age =\n| first_ascent =\n| easiest_route = Very steep trail<ref name=bivouac/>\n}}\n\n'''Kings Throne Peak''' is a {{Convert|1990|m|ft|lk=off|abbr=off|adj=on}} mountain [[summit]] in the Dalton Range of the [[Saint Elias Mountains]], in [[Kluane National Park and Reserve|Kluane National Park]] of [[Yukon]], [[Canada]]. The mountain is situated above the south shore of [[Kathleen Lake]], {{convert|7.2|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} southeast of [[Mount Worthington (Yukon)|Mount Worthington]] across the lake, and {{convert|27|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-southeast of [[Haines Junction, Yukon]]. The mountain can be seen from the [[Haines Highway]] as it prominently rises {{Convert|1250|m|ft|lk=off|abbr=off|adj=on}} above the lake. The mountain's descriptive name comes from how it is shaped by a [[cirque]] on the north aspect. A [[rock glacier]] descends from the cirque to the lake. A steep five kilometer trail provides access to the amphitheater, and an additional three kilometres on a beaten path reaches the summit via the east ridge. Based on the [[K\u00f6ppen climate classification]], Kings Throne Peak is located in a [[subarctic climate]] with long, cold, snowy winters, and mild summers.<ref name=Peel>{{cite journal | author = Peel, M. C. |author2=Finlayson, B. L. |author3=McMahon, T. A. |last-author-amp=yes | year = 2007 | title = Updated world map of the K\u00f6ppen\u2212Geiger climate classification | journal = Hydrol. Earth Syst. Sci. | volume = 11 | pages = 1633\u20131644 | issn = 1027-5606}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Mountains}}\n*[[List of mountains of Canada]]\n*[[Geography of Yukon]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[File:Kings Throne Peak, Kathleen Lake.jpg|thumb|center|440px|Kings Throne Peak and Kathleen Lake]]\n\n==External links==\n* Parks Canada website: [https://www.pc.gc.ca/en/pn-np/yt/kluane/activ/randonnee-hiking/kings-throne Kings Throne trail]\n* Flickr photo: [https://www.flickr.com/photos/ben_a/14440744537/in/album-72157645213868397/ View of the cirque]\n* Flickr photo: [https://www.flickr.com/photos/tvrdypa/43691157794/in/photolist-29yQB33-2592F47-YSAP3W-YDa7DY-269emM8-uh1srQ-frqSDW-K5TnP8-n6LV9U-G5tDRJ-dvmywV-2hGk7s7-a8vKoo-k7ZGST-c1amqf-kuQUeB-2fP1q7b-khTojV-ktfXjj-ku68a6-WU1uba-2g1XiNV-rkrpmR-MtuLHd-6MvtbH-8CAzWK-Ln6hhQ-cCGLhJ-6MvunZ-6MvpGp-6MzC5Q-cuPpv9-BBmLtd-MPVhba-8Pb8wW-75kMGb-RfgD4Q-d7MoWu-d7MbfS-7EabTs-d7N3Bh-PSUWyR-SnoSDr-syF63-DT1jYu-Hj5pgN-d7MGk7-EhKzyd-8eVpJw-Hj5S9f Kings Throne Peak with Kathleen Lake]\n\n[[Category:Mountains of Yukon]]\n[[Category:Saint Elias Mountains]]\n[[Category:Kluane National Park and Reserve]]\n", "name_user": "Ron Clausen", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kings_Throne_Peak"}
{"title_page": "Let's Get Married (song)", "text_new": "{{for|other songs of the same name|Let's Get Married (disambiguation)}}\n{{refimprove|date=January 2016}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Let's Get Married\n| cover      = Let's Get Married.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Jagged Edge (American group)|Jagged Edge]]\n| album      = [[J.E. Heartbreak]]\n| released   = February 2000\n| format     = [[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 1999\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n| length     = 4:23\n| label      = [[So So Def Recordings|So So Def]]\n| writer     = Brian Casey,  Brandon Casey, [[Jermaine Dupri]], [[Bryan-Michael Cox]]\n| producer   = [[Jermaine Dupri]]  & co-produced by [[Bryan-Michael Cox]]\n| prev_title = [[He Can't Love U]]\n| prev_year  = 1999\n| next_title = [[Promise (Jagged Edge song)|Promise]]\n| next_year  = 2000\n}}\n\n'''\"Let's Get Married\"''' is a song performed by American [[contemporary R&B]] group [[Jagged Edge (American group)|Jagged Edge]], from their album ''[[J.E. Heartbreak]]''. It spent three weeks at the top of the US R&B chart in 2000 and reached #11 on the US pop chart. The song is a slow love ballad about a man's desire to marry his love interest.\n\nThe remix features [[Joseph Simmons|DJ Run]] of [[Run-D.M.C.]] and samples the group's debut single \"[[It's Like That (Run\u2013D.M.C. song)|It's Like That]]\". The official video for the remix was directed by Bryan Barber.\n\nThe group performed the single at the [[kayfabe]] wedding of [[Theodore Long]] and [[Kristal Marshall]] on the September 21, 2007, episode of [[WWE Friday Night SmackDown]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/sdwedding/articles/jaggededgeready|title=Jagged Edge is ready for a wedding|last=Difino|first=Lennie|publisher=[[WWE]]|date=September 18, 2007|accessdate=April 19, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n===Peak positions===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (2000)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n